HEADWORD: Communicative
<hw>Com*mu"ni*ca*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>Communicatif</ets>, LL. <ets>communicativus</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Inclined to communicate; ready to impart to others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Determine, for the future, to be less
